The Alex Jones Show
Tuesday, 12 April 2011

Scheduled Guests
................

From the Infowars web site ::


Alex welcomes back to the show Robert M. Bowman, a former Director of Advanced Space Programs Development for the U.S. Air Force in the Ford and Carter administrations, and a former United States Air Force Lieutenant Colonel with 101 combat missions. He holds a Ph.D. in Aeronautics and Nuclear Engineering from the California Institute of Technology. 

Alex also talks with Christopher Busby, a British scientist and activist known for his work on the health effects of ionizing radiation. Busby is a Visiting Professor in the Faculty of Life and Health Sciences in the University of Ulster, Northern Ireland.
